# New tools — traffic & SEO first

When the user asks to add a toy, tool, or page to this site, **bias toward ideas that earn organic visits and clear search/share intent** — not only “fun” or technical novelty.

## Prefer tools that

- **Match real queries**: “how to…”, calculators, converters, checkers, validators, generators, timers, comparisons (things people type into Google).
- **Support long-tail copy**: specific `<title>`, `<meta name="description">`, H1, and body text that naturally include target phrases (without stuffing).
- **Are cite‑ and link‑worthy**: useful enough that blogs, docs, or social posts might link to them (utilities > pure toys unless the toy is highly shareable).
- **Differentiate**: avoid clones of ten identical free tools unless we add a clearer angle (speed, privacy, UX, niche audience).
- **Stay indexable**: real HTML pages with the same SEO stack as existing tools (`canonical`, Open Graph, Twitter, JSON-LD `WebApplication`, `robots` / `noindex` only when appropriate).

## Implementation checklist (do not skip)

- **Pick the folder from `category`:** `utility` → `tools/<slug>/`; **`game` | `visual` | `audio` | `wellness`** → `toys/<slug>/`. Paths in `tools-registry.json` must be `tools/<slug>/index.html` or `toys/<slug>/index.html` accordingly (run `node scripts/build-sitemap.cjs` after registry edits).
- Add the page under that folder: `index.html` + `styles.css` (and a local `.js` only if the script is large—otherwise inline is fine).
- In `<head>`, after `../../assets/styles.css`, link **`../../assets/tool-shell.css`**, then `styles.css`. **Do not** put tool-specific selectors or scripts in `assets/styles.css` or `assets/main.js`—those stay for the gallery shell (home, cards, footer, topbar).
- Register in `tools-registry.json` with **`category`**, **specific `shortDescription`**, **`tags`** (1–2 hyphenated role nouns; add **`TYPE_NL_PHRASES`** in `assets/main.js` for any new tag), and **`related`** (2–4 slugs that exist in the registry).
- On the page: `body data-tool-slug="<slug>"`, `<div id="toolCrossRoot" class="tool-cross-mount"></div>` before `</main>`, and `<script src="../../assets/site-chrome.js" defer></script>` + `<script src="../../assets/tool-cross.js" defer></script>` before `</body>`.
- Reuse the global header/footer, gtag, and **`https://onepagetoys.com/tools/...` or `.../toys/...`** canonical pattern matching the folder you chose.

## Before building

Offer **2–3 candidate ideas** in short form, each with one line on **who searches for it** and **what phrase cluster** it could capture. Let the user pick or combine — unless they already named the tool.

## Deprioritize for pure SEO goals

- Ultra-niche experiments with no search volume and no share hook.
- Duplicate functionality of an existing on-site tool without a new keyword angle.
